-- Primerica Board Authorizes $75 Million Share Buyback Plan
-- B y   S t e v e n   N o r t o n
-- 2012-08-07T20:07:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/primerica-board-authorizes-75-million-share-buyback-plan.html
Primerica Inc., the life insurer
formerly owned by Citigroup Inc., said it plans to buy back as
much as $75 million of its common stock.  Repurchases are expected to begin Aug. 10 and occur over
the next four months to six months, the Duluth, Georgia-based
company said today in a statement distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steven Norton in New York at 
 Snorton7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  